{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}Privacy Policy | Claudriel{% endblock %}

{% block styles %}
    body {
        min-height: 100vh;
        background:
            radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(107, 155, 255, 0.12), transparent 30%),
            linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0c10 0%, #131620 52%, #0a0c10 100%);
    }
    .privacy-shell {
        max-width: 780px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 3rem 1.4rem 5rem;
    }
    .privacy-shell h1 {
        font-family: var(--font-display);
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .privacy-shell .last-updated {
        color: var(--text-muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }
    .privacy-shell h2 {
        font-family: var(--font-display);
        font-size: 1.35rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        margin-top: 2.2rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
        color: var(--text-primary);
    }
    .privacy-shell p,
    .privacy-shell li {
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        line-height: 1.7;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    .privacy-shell ul {
        padding-left: 1.4rem;
        margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
    }
    .privacy-shell li {
        margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }
    .privacy-shell a {
        color: var(--accent-teal);
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }
    .privacy-shell a:hover {
        color: var(--text-primary);
    }
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <main class="privacy-shell">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {{ last_updated }}</p>

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            Claudriel ("we", "us", "our") is a personal operations platform that helps
            professionals manage commitments, schedules, and client context. This policy
            explains what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>When you use Claudriel, we may access the following data through Google APIs:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Gmail (read-only):</strong> Email metadata and message content to extract
                commitments, follow-ups, and context. We do not send, modify, or delete your emails.</li>
            <li><strong>Google Calendar (read-only):</strong> Calendar events to provide scheduling
                context in your daily brief. We do not create, modify, or delete your events through
                this scope.</li>
            <li><strong>Google Drive (read-only):</strong> Document metadata for context linking.
                We do not modify or delete your files.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Extract commitments and action items from your email conversations</li>
            <li>Generate daily briefings with your upcoming schedule and pending items</li>
            <li>Detect drifting commitments that may need your attention</li>
            <li>Provide contextual information about people and projects you work with</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Your data is processed solely to provide Claudriel's features to you. We do not
            sell, share, or use your data for advertising purposes.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Your data is stored on secured servers hosted in Canada</li>
            <li>Google OAuth tokens are encrypted at rest</li>
            <li>All connections use TLS encryption in transit</li>
            <li>We retain your data only as long as your account is active</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
            Claudriel uses the Anthropic API (Claude) to process text for commitment extraction
            and context analysis. Text sent to the API is not stored by Anthropic beyond the
            duration of the request. No other third parties receive your data.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> You can request a copy of all data we hold about you</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> You can request deletion of your account and all associated data</li>
            <li><strong>Revocation:</strong> You can disconnect Google services at any time from your
                Claudriel settings, which immediately revokes our access</li>
            <li><strong>Portability:</strong> You can export your data in standard formats</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Google API Services User Data Policy</h2>
        <p>
            Claudriel's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs adheres to the
            <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>,
            including the Limited Use requirements.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this policy from time to time. Significant changes will be communicated
            through the application. The "last updated" date at the top reflects the most recent revision.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
            For privacy questions or data requests, contact us at
            <a href="mailto:{{ contact_email }}">{{ contact_email }}</a>.
        </p>
    </main>
{% endblock %}
